about shutting down coke ovens led him to attend the rally even 
though he knew the union leadership backed the legislation its 
a big union a democratic union he said 
while the major steel companies oppose the bill the union says 
the measure provides enough time and leeway for steelmakers to 
avoid hardships 
under the bill steel producers that make extraordinary efforts 
to control leakage from coke ovens would be given until 2020 before 
noncomplying ovens would be closed 
the union believes the industry duped workers in a crude 
campaign of deception by making it seem there is a possibility of 
immediate job loss from the bill said union spokesman gary 
hubbard 
