democrats for theirs he also said the president is seeking a 2 
percent cut in the education budget 
rep harris fawell rill estimated that the democrats 
version would cost 50 billion in five years and said nobody in 
the budget committee could begin to take it seriously 
the senate in early february voted 928 to approve and send to 
the house the excellence in education act initially submitted by 
bush last spring 
the bill seeks to combat drugs in public schools establish a 
presidential merit schools program and increase aid to schools 
seeking to reduce dropout rates one controversial section would 
award 25 million in federal funds over three years to the recently 
established national board for professional teaching standards 
hawkins bill would increase by 1 billion the authorized amount 
for head start for fiscal 1991 fully fund the special supplemental 
food program for women infants and children by 1994 and expand the 
even start program it also would increase aid for dropout 
prevention deterring drug abuse and assisting the handicapped 
illiterate and disadvantaged 
