the first written arguments from harris lawyers normally due 
in 40 days must be submitted by april 13 remaining briefs from 
both sides will get an additional 17 days rather than 44 and the 
hearing is two weeks later may 14 
no deadline is set for the court to make its ruling 
the panel consists of judge john noonan who issued the order 
last friday blocking harris execution and judges arthur alarcon 
and melvin brunetti 
