a sikh religious symbol and refused to leave it outside 
militant sikh separatists who want to create an independent 
nation for their religious minority have killed more than 500 
people this year in punjab a prosperous northern farming state 
where they hold a slight majority 
tuesdays attack was one of the worst this year on march 7 a 
bomb and rifle attack by sikh militants killed 34 people in the 
predominantly hindu town of abohar 
batala a predominantly hindu town of 120000 people is 25 
miles northeast of amritsar a major center of the sikh separatist 
movement and site of the faiths holiest shrine the golden temple 
after the bombing hindu crowds went on a rampage and hurled 
stones at a police station 450 feet from the blast site said gur 
inder singh bhuller deputy inspector general of police he said 
five policemen were injured and their colleagues fired in the air 
to disperse the mob 
witnesses said the mobs set fire to several shops and vehicles 
and tried to torch a sikh gurdwara or place of worship 
punjab state police many of whom are sikhs were withdrawn from 
batala to stop the backlash some people accused police of not 
providing sufficient security during the ram navami celebrations 
members of the federal governments border security force were 
deployed in batala after the blast they patrolled on foot and in 
jeeps equipped with light machine guns 
senior police superintendent sk goel said the bomb was hidden 
in a motor scooter parked outside a cigarette kiosk he said he did 
not know if it had a timing device or was detonated by remote 
control 
goel said the bomb probably was planted by sikh radicals other 
officials speaking on condition of anonmity also blamed sikh 
extremists 
many of the victims were blown to pieces fragments of bodies 
and bloodstained vegetables were flung across the market 
there was a loud sound then the entire area was covered with 
dark smoke and fire which rose as high as electric poles food 
vendor pre nath said from his hospital bed in amritsar where he 
was treated for leg injuries 
the violent sikh separatist campaign began in 1982 in punjab 
where more than 1800 people were killed in the separatist violence 
last year 
nationwide sikhs make up only 2 percent of the population of 
880 million while hindus comprise 82 percent sikhs whose faith 
has roots in hinduism and islam say they are culturally and 
politically discriminated against by hindus 
