about the basic law saying it will impede democratic reform in 
hong kong and give beijing arbitrary powers to declare a state of 
emergency 
the amendments to the 1979 joint venture law were seen as a 
gesture to foreign investors wary of doing business in china after 
the crackdown 
they stipulate that the lifetime of a joint venture previously 
limited to 30 years can be openended and guarantee that such 
ventures will never be nationalized under normal circumstances 
the law was also amended to say a foreign partner could be 
elected chairman of the venture previously the chinese side 
headed the board even when the foreign partners equity share 
exceeded 50 percent 
