called for a direct 11 conversion to ease the withdrawal pains of 
unemployment and high prices as east germany sheds it socialist 
system 
but the social democrats still are opposed to the more 
conservative elements in de maizieres coalition much of the 
wrangling has been over the distribution of cabinet posts in a 
newly formed government 
there are indeed as before substantial differences but these 
are not insurmountable lawmaker richard schroeder leader of the 
social democrat faction in parliament said tuesday 
social democrat spokesman guenther krug said there would not be 
a coalition if the social democrats positions were not adequately 
represented in a coalition platform expected to be hammered out 
during negotiations 
the first openly elected lawmaking body in the nations history 
is to convene on thursday in what will likely be a ceremonial 
session with little substantive political action 
since east germans toppled the hardline government of erich 
honecker in october a communist caretaker has been running the 
economically troubled nation 
the talks have been hamstrung over allegations that many members 
of the new parliament cooperated with or worked for the former 
secret police of the old stalinist leadership 
social democrat leader ibrahim boehme resigned over the weekend 
because of such allegations although he has denied involvement 
de maiziere has denied similar allegations 
