he denied that mrs marcos had any part in the dealings on which 
the charges are based mrs marcos never wrote a check in her 
life she never paid a bill in her life spence told the jury 
spence sought to trace the origins of the new york real estate 
deals to cia concern in the early 1980s that the philippines 
would fall to the communists 
according to spence bush then vice president visited manila 
in 1981 and urged marcos to abandon negotiations with libyan leader 
moammar gadhafi on an oil investment deal and put the money instead 
into american property 
the evidence in this case is that the cia was aware of every 
transaction that took place in this case spence said 
earlier assistant us attorney debra livingston charged that 
the marcoses were partners in crime who used accomplices fake 
documents and 13 shell corporations to steal 168 million in 
philippine government funds and defraud us banks of 165 million 
more she said the couple used some of the money to buy four 
expensive pieces of new york real estate and other luxury items 
she said mrs marcos treated the new york branch of the 
philippine national bank as her own personal piggy bank every 
time she descended on new york she cracked it open taking 
bundles and bundles of cash 
livingston said khashoggi 54 entered the picture after mrs 
aquino replaced marcos in 1986 and her government won a us court 
order to prohibit any further transactions involving the four 
buildingss 
khashoggi she said committed fraud and obstructed justice by 
fabricating documents showing that he not the marcoses had owned 
the buildings for several years 
if convicted mrs marcos could get up to 50 years in prison and 
a 1 million fine khashoggi once described as the worlds richest 
man could receive up to 10 years in prison and a 500000 fine if 
convicted 
spence said mrs marcos never lost sight of her humble origins 
she was beloved by the people he said if she took 30 
minutes to dress for a head of state she took an hour to dress for 
the little people 
spence said mrs marcos had been unfairly treated for having had 
more than 1000 pairs of shoes left behind in manila 
one thing that made up this woman is how long she was 
barefoot he said he added however that most of the shoes were 
given to her by local shoe manufacturers and most of them didnt 
fit 
</TEXT>
