<TEXT>
a molten flow from the kilauea volcano 
surged beneath a house today destroyed it within an hour and 
threatened other residences in an 82home subdivision 
it was the first kalapana gardens home destroyed since lava 
enter the subdivision tuesday and the first destroyed by molten 
rock since a december 1986 flow wiped out dozens of homes in the 
subdivison 
tenants of the rented house moved out monday said ed torrison 
whose home was 50 feet away in the path of flow the lava passed 
within several feet of two homes tuesday and moved on to threaten 
two others besides the one engulfed at 6 am today 
like his neighbors torrison moved belongings out of his home 
that done he sat back to await the verdict of pele the hawaiian 
volcano goddess 
everybodys nervous but nobody wants to admit it said 
resident dennis gregory people dont freak out here this is 
hawaii everybody is taking it slow and easy 
residents cheered the thunderous explosions of methane from 
inside the flow and the flames that flashed through trees as the 
lava cut a swath through the dense foliage 
several people watched the approaching lava from the balcony of 
the closest home occasionally pitching beer bottles into the 
molten rock and laughing at repeated jokes about declining property 
values in the neighborhood 
its a party atmosphere said craig heiser a neighbor 
helping to evacuate residents you cant do anything about it so 
just enjoy it 
the authorities said residents of 57 homes had been evacuated 
and the entire community was on alert meaning an evacuation order 
could be issued within 72 hours in addition to the subdivision 
homes there are 43 other houses in the area 
whats happening now is the worstcase scenario said hawaii 
county civil defense administrator harry kim 
the lava late tuesday overran a rock wall into the backyard of a 
home and filled the sevenfoot gully in the yard its edge stopped 
just four feet from the home before it stopped moving sideways and 
moved down a gully 
the flow moved 100 yards down the gully overnight to threaten 
three more homes 
lava had come within 20 feet of one of those three homes by 
early today it surged forward burned a backyard tool shed then 
stopped as it built up a crust but it could liquefy and surge in 
another direction 
another flow to the east was about a halfmile above the 
subdivision kim said it appeared the flow would not threaten homes 
for at least another day 
civil defense and red cross officials opened a shelter at a 
community center 12 miles to the east 
