ambassador jack f matlock jr accompanied shevardnadze to 
washington for the talks which will culminate friday with a 
meeting with bush at the white house 
his prospective reassignment as the soviet ambassador to 
washington is part of a revamping of the principal overseas 
assignments in the soviet foreign service it is not considered a 
reflection on dubinin who succeeded longtime soviet ambassador 
anatoly f dobrynin both envoys were known for their affability 
dubinin who entered the soviet foreign service in 1965 
