unit described the ebb and flow of drug markets as a cat and 
mouse game 
in denver capt rudy sandoval of the police vice and narcotics 
bureau said weve still got crack houses but theyre 
underground theyre not on the street bothering people like they 
used to 
the street drug market in new orleans has changed but the 
overall situation hasnt improved said capt chuck ladell chief 
of detectives 
there are more of them now but they are more discreet 
ladell said 
despite some increases in prices for kilos of cocaine street 
prices have remained relatively stable averaging 100 a gram 
nationwide police said 
