psychiatric treatment at denver general hospital said the number 
of patients showing up in the emergency room with cocainerelated 
problems appears to be leveling off after years of steadily 
increasing 
over the past few years weve seen an increase in the number 
of cocaine addicts but no particular increase in the last year 
dilts said 
