the dollar fell against most major currencies in 
european trading this morning 
gold was lower in thin and aimless trading 
in tokyo the dollar closed at 15890 yen down 005 yen from 
tuesdays close later in london the dollar traded at 15875 yen 
the dollar started higher following overnight gains in new york 
but the currency gradually fell in tokyo as market players mainly 
life insurance and securities houses sold the dollar against the 
yen in an attempt to reduce their dollar holdings ahead of the 
meeting of the group of seven key currency nations scheduled for 
april 7 in paris said mamoru tabata a dealer with the mitsui 
taiyo kobe bank in tokyo 
market players began to reduce their dollar holdings in case 
the g7 meeting comes up with something they had not predicted 
although nothing special is expected at the moment he said 
other dollar rates at midmorning compared with late tuesdays 
quotes included 16980 west german marks down from 17005 
15028 swiss francs down from 15035 57030 french francs down 
from 57410 19100 dutch guilders down from 19150 124700 
italian lire down from 125400 and 11675 canadian dollars up 
from 11660 
in london the british pound was quoted at 16400 compared 
with 16345 late tuesday 
