natural gas futures were traded on the new york 
mercantile exchange for the first time in what analysts termed a 
light but successful session 
about 920 contracts for future delivery of natural gas traded 
hands during tuesdays initial session 
the volume was far below the 50000 to 70000 crude oil futures 
traded daily on the exchange but analysts said the important 
traders were there 
there certainly was trade participation which is important in 
a new contract said andrew lebow an energy market analyst in 
new york with edamp f man international futures inc 
everybody in the industry was watching it and i think its 
going to be a successful contract he said 
the contract for june delivery of natural gas traded from 158 
to 1655 during the session and settled at 1635 per million 
british thermal units 
futures contracts are used by producers and consumers of raw 
commodities to hedge against financial risk by locking in prices in 
advance speculators also play futures markets in hopes of 
profiting from the constant change in prices 
