<TEXT>
atlantabased contel corp said it planned a 
major restructuring of its telephone operations division that could 
eliminate about 600 jobs across the country 
the cutbacks which represent about 4 percent of contels 
telephone operations staff will take place over the next two 
years they are expected to be achieved largely through attrition 
and voluntary separation programs 
under the restructuring plan contel said it would combine the 
telephone operations from three regions and 12 divisions into six 
multistate operating groups reporting directly to headquarters 
the restructuring centralizes policy setting and allows 
decisions to be made at the local level said brian farley a 
contel spokesman 
although contel has not determined the cost of employee 
separation programs farley said the company does not expect the 
restructuring to have an impact on financial results 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

