<TEXT>
takeover strategist carl icahn says spinning 
off usx corps steel division would increase shareholders returns 
by about 29 percent 
the new york financier told stockholders in a letter tuesday he 
estimated that shares in a separate energy company would be worth 
39 while stock in a steel unit would be worth 9 
usxs stock closed tuesday at 3712 a share up 150 in new 
york stock exchange composite trading 
usx spokesman william keslar declined to comment on the letter 
today saying the company was studying it 
icahn the largest stockholder of usx with 34 million shares or 
1329 percent has asked the shareholders for a nonbinding vote on 
a proposal to spin off the steel division and call the new company 
us steel 
fourfifths of the new company would become a dividend to usx 
shareholders who also would own marathon oil co and smaller usx 
interests 
the rest of the new company would go to new investors icahns 
plan would include no more than 15 billion in longterm debt 
incurred by the steel division 
the stockholders will vote on icahns proposal at usxs annual 
meeting may 7 
usx has opposed the plan executives said it would make marathon 
and us steel more vulnerable to slumps in either the energy or 
steel industries 
usx has said 65 percent of its revenue comes from marathon 
while 31 percent come from steel operations 
icahn who is the chairman of trans world airlines said in the 
letter usx could properly structure the division of its companies 
to make them essentially taxfree to the company and its 
stockholders the plan would preserve net operating losses of usx 
he said 
usx chairman charles a corry recently told wall street analysts 
icahns plan had pitfalls because the company could lose tax 
credits resulting from steel losses in the early 1980s 
</TEXT>
