<TEXT>
unsecured creditors of eastern airlines 
frustrated by the companys mounting losses and plans to reduce 
debt payments have agreed to seek the appointment of a special 
trustee to find a buyer for the carrier 
the unsecured creditors committee voted unanimously tuesday to 
reject easterns latest reorganization proposal which would give 
them only 25 cents for each dollar owed a majority of the 
creditors also voted to seek the appointment of a special trustee 
sources close to the committee said 
this group has had it and theyre not going to take it 
anymore one of the sources said 
the move puts the creditors in alliance with easterns unions 
which have sought a trustee since miamibased eastern filed for 
bankruptcy protection on march 9 1989 the chapter 11 filing came 
five days after the start of a crippling strike by pilots flight 
attendants and machinists 
until recently the creditors had been supportive of eastern 
efforts to rebuild the unions meanwhile have argued that a 
trustee should take over the management of eastern from frank 
lorenzo chairman of easterns parent texas air corp they accuse 
lorenzo of draining easterns assets into its sister carrier 
continental airlines and texas air 
in a meeting in new york tuesday with officials of eastern and 
texas air the committee of unsecured creditors rejected easterns 
plan to repay 25 percent of the 980 million it owes them the 
sources said 
the creditors committee authorized its attorneys to ask the 
us bankruptcy court to appoint a special trustee to sell the 
airline said the sources who spoke on condition of anonymity the 
committee dropped an earlier threat to press for a liquidation of 
eastern 
the unsecured creditors include aircraft manufacturers such as 
boeing co and airbus industrie and jet engine makers like general 
electric co 
the plan presented today serves the creditors far better than 
any alternative transaction including liquidation or sale of the 
airline both of which are exceedingly remote said eastern 
spokesman robin matell in miami 
referring to the creditors move for a trustee he said 
assuming that is not a negotiating ploy there is no legal or 
policy basis for the appointment of a trustee 
separately tuesday us bankruptcy judge burton r lifland 
adjourned until may 9 consideration of the unions request for a 
trustee which previously had been deferred about half a dozen 
times 
the creditors committee could present its trustee demand at 
that time the creditors also may be hardening their stance in an 
effort to extract fuller payment from eastern 
last july eastern promised creditors full repayment of debts 
with interest it slashed that proposal in late january to 10 cents 
on the dollar in cash when the airline emerges from bankruptcy 
protection and another 70 percent over the following 10 years 
without interest 
after the creditors balked eastern reached agreement with them 
in midfebruary on a plan that would pay 50 cents on the dollar 
upon emerging from bankruptcy but eastern told the creditors last 
week it couldnt fulfill that agreement because of problems in 
attracting passengers and rebuilding its operations 
in response the creditors committee privately passed a 
resolution last week authorizing its attorneys to seek the 
appointment of a trustee to replace current management and to 
propose a plan of liquidation 
the creditors attorneys would take such action if texas air 
refused to cover easterns future operating losses according to 
the resolution 
at tuesdays meeting robert ferguson a vice president of texas 
air told the creditors the company would agree to cover only a 
portion of easterns losses the sources said 
the carriers latest plan called for paying 10 cents on the 
dollar in the form of eastern notes guaranteed by continental 
another 10 cents in texas air notes and the remaining 5 cents in 
cash the sources said 
this time the creditors responded by calling for a sale of 
eastern rather than a liquidation earlier speculation about a 
possible liquidation had hurt the airline by scaring away 
passengers and travel agents 
they took out the l word a source said 
the creditors have been soliciting possible buyers behind the 
scenes in recent weeks sources say 
the creditors committee also was concerned that calls for 
liquidation could jeopardize the proposed sale of easterns prized 
latin american routes to rival american airlines for 349 million 
proceeds from that sale are central to easterns plan to rebuild 
the transaction was approved by lifland last thursday but still 
must be approved by the transportation department a decision by 
the department is expected by friday 
a committee of the airlines preferred shareholders also has 
expressed disapproval with easterns reorganization and repayment 
proposals 
</TEXT>
