of a new europe when it assumes the ecs rotating sixthmonth 
presidency on july 1 
the events of the first months of this year are already 
compelling us to step up our pace in the wake of german 
reunification which is moving ahead of european unification said 
a working paper on italys ec agenda 
the document presented at a news conference by de michelis 
described 1990 as an era comparable only to the aftermath of 
world war ii 
common market leaders are scheduled to open a special conference 
in italy in december to rewrite parts of their founding 1957 treaty 
of rome the revisions will clear the way for economic and monetary 
union including creation of a regional central bank and a common 
currency 
de michelis said the monetary conference will begin dec 14 and 
should be concluded within the first six months of 1991 rather 
than the end of the year as originally envisioned 
he said italy wants a conference on political union to be held 
simultaneously with the monetary talks these negotiations would 
reform ec institutions extend the powers of the european 
parliament and strengthen political cooperation with the aim of 
shaping a common foreign policy 
de michelis said the political treaty could be implemented as 
early as the next european parliament elections in 1994 he gave no 
details of the new political structure which has been variously 
described as the european union or the european federation 
although british prime minister margaret thatcher has opposed 
monetary and political union de michelis said the prevailing 
opinion among ec members favors the unity programs and that on 
the whole the community is moving toward harmony and away from 
dissonance 
with the ec scheduled to become a single market by the end of 
1992 italy will seek to push through approval this year of most of 
the remaining provisions necessary to meet the deadline de 
michelis said the 12 nations have already approved 60 percent of 
the 279 directives but the italian working paper said a strong 
political will and a further stepping up of our pace is necessary 
</TEXT>
