sales of north americanmade cars and trucks rose 
29 percent in late march compared with last year the automakers 
reported wednesday but the increase stemmed largely from gains by 
general motors corp 
auto industry analysts said the results were encouraging 
nonetheless they said it was unclear whether the 6monthlong slump 
was coming to an end 
vehicle sales by ford motor co and chrysler corp fell by 38 
percent and 166 percent respectively during the march 2131 period 
this year compared with last year 
gms latemarch car and truck sales rose 61 percent mostly 
because of its light trucks including minivans that were offered 
with buyerluring incentives for the first time 
on march 22 gm began offering 1000 rebates and on its 
threevehicle line of minivans the chevrolet lumina apv the 
pontiac trans sport and the oldsmobile silhouette the program runs 
until may 2 
combined car and truck sales for the nine major us automakers 
rose to a daily average of 43688 during the period this year 
compared with an average of 42451 during the same time last year 
car sales were up 27 percent and lighttruck sales rose 32 
percent during the period compared with a relatively soft period in 
1989 
however for all of march and for the first three months of this 
year with imported vehicles included sales lagged behind the 
corresponding periods in 1989 
