pepsicola co is giving the phrase pop art a 
new slant with four jazzy new labels for cans of its flagship soft 
drink brand as part of a promotion to kick off the summer 
the nations secondlargest soft drink company is calling its 
special package designs cool cans the new packages are showing 
up in stores in the northwest and will be available nationally by 
early may the somers nybased company said 
one of the new designs features a drawing of a surfer in in an 
array of red yellow and blue colors along with the regular pepsi 
label 
in another a drawing of a womans face appears on the label 
with the pepsi logo reflected in her sunglasses 
a third design called neon uses a black rather than a white 
background while a fourth called party incorporates red white 
and blue streamers dots stars and diamonds into the label 
pepsi officials said 12 billion cool cans will be 
distributed during the promotion they will account for more than 
half of the pepsi cans on store shelves for the six to eightweek 
period which ends in june 
