with a longestablished label because loyal customers might 
mistakenly feel that signals a change in the product itself 
but michael simpson executive vice president for marketing and 
national sales at pepsicola said pepsi tried to avoid that 
problem by incorporating some element of the original trademark 
into the new designs 
he said in consumer tests of the new labels people clearly 
understood it was pepsi there is no missing the pepsi logo even 
the colors are consistent 
he said the new designs appeal to consumers of all ages 
its a very exciting contemporary look simpson said 
