<TEXT>
paul newman was alternately portrayed 
as an egotistical movie star who reneged on a promise and a modest 
philanthropist before the salad dressing suit brought by a 
delicatessen owner went to a jury wednesday 
there are people in the world who operate on a different 
level richard albrecht attorney for deli owner julius gold 
told jurors in his closing arguments some do so with grace and 
some do so with raw exhibition of power 
its the race car thing albrecht added referring to 
newmans love of racecar driving as the actor sat smirking in the 
back of the courtroom 
gold is seeking an 8 percent stake in newmans own inc and 
salad king inc claiming he spent four years advising newman and 
helping him establish the food businesses 
newmans lawyer portrayed the actor as an honest businessman who 
started the two companies as a way to raise money for charity he 
played down the portrayal of newman as a rich celebrity by 
referring to golds success as a businessman 
gold is not some poor little shopkeeper attorney w patrick 
ryan said its not david and goliath get that out of your 
head 
the sixmember jury began deliberations at midafternoon and 
were dismissed for the day about an hour and 45 minutes later 
gold said he was confident he would prevail 
i would think the longer the jury stays out in this case the 
better it would look for me gold said 
gold is suing newman writer ae hotchner and the two food 
businesses claiming they reneged on a promise to give him stock in 
return for his participation in the development and marketing of 
newmans own salad dressing 
an earlier trial ended in a mistrial in 1988 when the jury 
mistakenly received depositions that had not been admitted as 
evidence 
superior court judge george n thim told jurors they must 
conclude that gold had an oral contract with newman and the other 
defendants if they are to find in favor of gold 
newman who has been in court almost every day since the trial 
began march 20 contends that golds only participation was to sell 
some of the dressing in his westport store 
newman and hotchner started newmans own on a whim beginning 
with salad dressing that newman originally made in the basement of 
his westport home and later expanding into spaghetti sauce popcorn 
and lemonade 
all profits 28 million to date go to charity the companies 
had a record 42 million in sales last year up from 36 million in 
1988 
