<TEXT>
circle k corp the nations secondlargest 
convenience store chain said late wednesday it has reached an 
agreement in principle with its main lenders to restructure part of 
its 13 billion debt 
circle k accumulated much of its debt during a rapid expansion 
that saw the company grow from about 1000 stores in 1984 to 4685 
last year 
the company said previously it might have to seek bankruptcy 
protection from creditors if it could not work out a debt 
restructuring last week the company reported it lost more than 
40 million on operations during the quarter ended jan 31 
circle k said the agreement involved its bank lenders a 
committee of holders of 200 million circle k senior secured notes 
and american financial corp circle ks largest shareholder and a 
creditor 
the agreement envisions that the parties will enter into a 
standstill agreement that would be effective the earlier of either 
oct 31 or the successful completion of the companys financial 
restructuring the company said 
until then the banks bondholders and american financial 
would defer all principal and interest payments on their 
respective obligations and waive any existing defaults under their 
current loan agreements circle k said 
the standstill agreement would require circle k by oct 31 to 
buy back at least 90 percent of its 510 million in subordinated 
debt circle k said terms of a buyback havent been determined 
yet it said 
the company said the standstill agreement is subject to approval 
by remaining noteholders 
ray cox a circle k spokesman declined to comment further 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

